Subject: [PATCH] ia64/sn: use hcdp_phys instead of efi.hcdp in sn_scan_pcdp()

In v5.7, Ard Biesheuvel's EFI cleanup series moved HCDP and MPS table
handling from the generic struct efi into ia64-local code.  The hcdp
member was removed from struct efi and replaced with a global
unsigned long hcdp_phys in arch/ia64/kernel/efi.c.

Update sn_scan_pcdp() to use the new hcdp_phys variable instead of
the removed efi.hcdp member.

---
 arch/ia64/sn/kernel/setup.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/ia64/sn/kernel/setup.c
+++ b/arch/ia64/sn/kernel/setup.c
@@ -321,11 +321,11 @@
 	struct pcdp *pcdp;
 	struct pcdp_device_desc device;
 	struct pcdp_interface_pci if_pci;
-	extern struct efi efi;
+	extern unsigned long hcdp_phys;
 
-	if (efi.hcdp == EFI_INVALID_TABLE_ADDR)
+	if (hcdp_phys == EFI_INVALID_TABLE_ADDR)
 		return;		/* no hcdp/pcdp table */
 
-	pcdp = __va(efi.hcdp);
+	pcdp = __va(hcdp_phys);
 
 	if (pcdp->rev < 3)
